bio.experienceSummary: I've been babysitting since I was 12 years old (I am now 26). I also come from a large family with 5 siblings, so I have my fair share of experience at home as well. I have watched children of all ages, from newborns to 13-year-old. I have worked in a child care center as well as obtained experience as an Au pair, living and working with a family in Canada. Multiple children are no problem for me and I love pets. I generally clean up around the house while there, especially after I've prepared food. I also help with schoolwork.

As a nurturing and experienced childcare provider with a decade of experience, I'm passionate about fostering children's growth and development. My calm and friendly demeanor creates a safe and welcoming environment for your little ones.

I maintain open lines of communication with parents, providing regular updates on their child's day and promptly addressing any concerns. With my background in early childhood development and certifications in First Aid and CPR, you can trust that your child will receive the utmost care and attention.

Whether it's engaging in outdoor games, educational activities, or technology-based learning, I tailor my approach to each child's unique interests and needs. I believe in supporting families and providing reliable childcare, allowing parents peace of mind knowing their children are in capable hands.

Let's connect and explore how I can be a positive addition to your family's journey.

I have been nannying for years and have been hired through care. com in the past. I have cared for multiple children and am able to tutor, play, supervise, and entertain children for long periods of time. I have cared for children from a few months old to 13-years-old. I am an outgoing person who loves kids and feels like a kid at heart. I am organized, responsible, and patient with people I am working for and people I am working with. I have a passion for working with kids and I would love to help your family!

description.displayText:
Maggie has taken great care of our 6 month old daughter over the last 3 months. She has also watched our 2.5 year old son during this time and he has really enjoyed spending time with her.

Maggie has been 100% reliable, always on time, flexible, and willing to work long hours as needed. She takes direction exceptionally well; listens carefully to understand what you need, then does exactly that. 

She has been gentle, caring, and patient with our baby, which were our priorities for a caregiver. She paid close attention to what she needed, learned how to keep her fed, well-rested, and happy, and helped us establish a solid routine.

I would absolutely re-hire Maggie in the future and recommend her without hesitation!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello!

My name is Sam and I am based in Atlanta, Georgia. I currently work full time for ESPN, but would love to help families during my offseason and downtime with child care.

Throughout high school and college I worked at a daycare- teaching/reading & creating a positive and fun environment for kids aged 1-5. On the side, I babysat for a family with newborn twins for a few years. 

I am very active & like to incorporate that in my childcare as well. Whether that's playing soccer in the front yard, helping a 1-year-old climb the stairs (with my assistance of course), or simply dancing to some Miss Rachel in the living room. Always a blast under my supervision!

One thing you should know about me is I have a ton of tattoos. I feel like this can come as a shock to some people when first seeing me. Absolutely none of them are offensive or distasteful! And no, no neck or face! But I know some families are not open to having their child exposed to this kind of self expression/art.

I'm an elementary school teacher with years of experience and certification in first aid, CPR, and AED. I'm passionate about helping kids learn and grow in a safe, nurturing environment. As an experienced babysitter, I'm comfortable with all aspects of childcare, and my top priority is always the safety and well-being of the children in my care. I'm flexible and willing to work with your schedule and travel to your home or accompany your family on outings. Thank you for considering me for your babysitting needs.

I am currently a project manager but was formerly a special education teacher with several years of nannying experience. I have always enjoyed working with children and watching them learn and grow. I have several years of experience with infants and have worked extensively with school age children as well. I can help with homework, light house keeping, and other chores as well.

My name is Maddie and I am 22 years old from Chicago. I recently graduated college with honors at Ohio University. I am moving to Atlanta the first week of January 2021 and am seeking a full-time nannying position. I am an experienced caretaker who has nannied for five different families at different points in my life. I have worked with ages 0-16 and am very skilled at what I do. My goal as a nanny is to be an integral part of the children's development. It is important to me that I form a close relationship with the family unit. I always make it known that I am willing to run any errands that make a parent's life easier. I am extremely self-sufficient and confident that I am an asset. Additionally, I am a very proficient cook who enjoys providing healthy meals all throughout the day. I often like to get the kids involved and make it fun! I am pretty creative when it comes to other activities as well. Thank you for the consideration and feel free to reach out with any questions!

description.displayText: Maddie was our weekend/weeknight sitter when she was in high school. This summer, while home from college, she's been our nanny. Our girls adore Maddie! She's fun, playful, responsible, always has a smile and great disposition. We wish Maddie was staying in Chicago and could stick with us through the school year. Any family would be lucky to have her!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi! My name is Evelyn and I have over five years of caregiving experience working with children, adults, and the elderly, including those with special needs. I am passionate about providing compassionate, personalized care that fosters emotional, mental, and physical well-being. Whether I'm helping children with homework, assisting adults with daily tasks, or providing companionship to the elderly, I approach every situation with patience, empathy, and dedication.
As a bilingual caregiver (Spanish and English), I can communicate effectively with families from diverse backgrounds. My caregiving style is adaptable to meet the unique needs of each individual, from children needing structured routines to elderly clients requiring gentle assistance.

With me, your children will receive appropriate care, and I'm willing to do additional other tasks if requested. Personally, I'm an organizer, planner, and multitasker, so minimum supervision is required. With all my skills and experience, I'm able to provide a supervised, safe, and stable environment for your little ones at your home

bio.experienceSummary: Over the last 10 years, I have worked as a home respite care provider, Special Education Teacher for learners with disabilities, Special Education Consultant and Coach, and Early Intervention Specialist working with babies birth-3 years old. My passions include Augmentative and Alternative Communication or AAC, Multi-sensory learning, Early Childhood literacy experiences, presuming competence, and most importantly, having fun! I am looking for summer positions to keep me busy before starting school in the fall!
